  "text": "iv) Brigham and Women's Hospital, Harvard Medical School [CITATION_1] Consists of 181 samples of malignant tissue, where 31 -malignant pleural mesothelioma and 150 -adenocarcinoma. Samples were divided in two sets: training (sixteen samples of each cancer type) and testing (the remaining 149 samples). Each sample is presented by expression levels of 12,533 genes. The task is to make a binary classification of malignant pleural mesothelioma and adenocarcinoma. :http://dx.doi.org/10.7314/APJCP.2016.17.2.835 ",
